The distribution of the lesions in the 36 patients with confirmed COVID-19 pneumonia was as follows: right lower lobe (26/36, 72.2%), left lower lobe (24/36, 66.7%),left upper lobe (20/36, 55.6%), right middle lobe (20/36, 55.6%) and right upper lobe (19/36, 52.7%), The distribution patterns were as follows: peripheral distribution (26/36, 72.2%) and central distribution (10/36, 27.8%). Except for 11 patients (11/36, 30.6%) with a single lesion, the majority of patients (25/36, 69.4%) had more multiple CT abnormalities. Compared to the control group, peripheral distribution was more common in the COVID-19 pneumonia group (P < 0.05), with a random distribution in all lobes (Fig. 2
). In patients without COVID-19 pneumonia, lower lobes distribution was more common than upper lungs location (Table 2
).
